WEBVTT

1
00:00:49.042 --> 00:00:53.042 line:82%
TOMORROW MAY NEVER COME.

2
00:01:05.417 --> 00:01:06.430 line:82%
New York...

3
00:01:08.708 --> 00:01:10.667 line:82%
...one of the biggest cities
in the world...

4
00:01:13.667 --> 00:01:16.542 line:82%
Every breath and heartbeat of the city
is filled with speed.

5
00:01:23.550 --> 00:01:25.417 line:82%
People are always in a hurry here.

6
00:01:26.083 --> 00:01:29.292 line:82%
They are in a hurry to leave home,
in a hurry to get to the office,

7
00:01:29.625 --> 00:01:32.130 line:82%
always in a hurry to be
a step ahead of life.

8
00:01:32.955 --> 00:01:35.500 line:82%
There is no place for anyone
who can't cope here.

9
00:01:39.167 --> 00:01:42.833 line:82%
Miles away from India,
this city is infested with Indians.

10
00:01:43.485 --> 00:01:46.500 line:82%
In fact, they say every fourth face
in New York is an Indian.

11
00:01:47.167 --> 00:01:48.240 line:82%
One more thing...

12
00:01:48.370 --> 00:01:50.595 line:82%
By the way, that's me.

13
00:02:51.630 --> 00:02:54.208 line:82%
This city taught me to be independent,

14
00:02:54.667 --> 00:02:56.958 line:82%
it taught me to fulfill
my responsibilities,

15
00:02:57.150 --> 00:02:59.042 line:82%
taught me to face life,

16
00:02:59.875 --> 00:03:01.458 line:82%
but it couldn't teach me to love.

17
00:03:02.458 --> 00:03:03.667 line:82%
Where was the time?

18
00:03:04.417 --> 00:03:06.333 line:82%
Whenever I watched the city from afar,

19
00:03:06.930 --> 00:03:08.792 line:82%
I felt my father was closer.

20
00:03:11.208 --> 00:03:14.375 line:82%
Whenever I missed him, I came here.

21
00:03:18.583 --> 00:03:23.850 line:82%
I am Naina Catherine Kapur
and this is my story.

22
00:03:32.250 --> 00:03:34.007 line:82%
But try and understand my problem.

23
00:03:35.318 --> 00:03:37.406 line:82%
I must have the loan extension please.

24
00:03:39.437 --> 00:03:41.584 line:82%
I know the resturant is centerly situated.

25
00:03:41.708 --> 00:03:44.833 line:82%
But there's competition around, Mr. Shah.

26
00:03:45.042 --> 00:03:48.792 line:82%
My mother, Jennifer.
After Papa passed away,

27
00:03:48.875 --> 00:03:51.195 line:82%
the entire responsibility
of the family fell on her.

28
00:03:51.667 --> 00:03:55.020 line:82%
But she never allowed us to ever
feel the burden of her sorrows.

29
00:03:55.901 --> 00:03:59.783 line:82%
- Thank you! I...
- I'm home.

30
00:04:01.515 --> 00:04:02.750 line:82%
Where were you?

31
00:04:03.833 --> 00:04:04.875 line:82%
Central Park.

32
00:04:05.333 --> 00:04:06.333 line:82%
Central Park? Why?

33
00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:08.583 line:82%
- To meet someone.
- Who?

34
00:04:08.708 --> 00:04:09.898 line:82%
To meet my boyfriend.

35
00:04:10.329 --> 00:04:12.163 line:82%
Bills! Bills! Bills!

36
00:04:12.994 --> 00:04:14.788 line:82%
Private and confidential.

37
00:04:15.390 --> 00:04:17.144 line:82%
What is this?
It's Sweetu's mail again.

38
00:04:17.262 --> 00:04:19.682 line:82%
When'll the mailman understand
that we are Kapur with a U.

39
00:04:19.745 --> 00:04:21.458 line:82%
and they are Kapoor with an O?
He always--

40
00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:23.400 line:82%
Were you crying?

41
00:04:24.333 --> 00:04:25.387 line:82%
No, you were crying.

42
00:04:25.459 --> 00:04:26.563 line:82%
No, Mom.

43
00:04:26.640 --> 00:04:30.417 line:82%
Mother and I,
we lied to each other every day.

44
00:04:30.583 --> 00:04:31.625 line:82%
Spinster Girl?

45
00:04:32.895 --> 00:04:35.304 line:82%
Kunwari kudi marriage bureau,
what's this?

46
00:04:35.385 --> 00:04:36.833 line:82%
Why don't you ask your grandmother?

47
00:04:36.917 --> 00:04:39.042 line:82%
It must be some new plan
to find you a groom.

48
00:04:39.125 --> 00:04:42.137 line:82%
But I don't want to get married!
Why doesn't grandmother leave me alone?

49
00:04:42.225 --> 00:04:43.500 line:82%
Why doesn't she just leave?

50
00:04:43.981 --> 00:04:45.735 line:82%
Mom! Where's she?

51
00:04:46.333 --> 00:04:47.335 line:82%
It's going to be eight.+

52
00:04:49.136 --> 00:04:50.677 line:82%
Hi Guys, 10 seconds to go.

53
00:04:53.218 --> 00:04:55.368 line:82%
8 seconds to go.

54
00:04:55.452 --> 00:04:59.083 line:82%
4,3,2,1.
Bang!

55
00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:02.475 line:82%
My grandmother, Lajjo.
She had three dreams.

56
00:05:02.542 --> 00:05:05.000 line:82%
One, that New York
becomes a part of Punjab.

57
00:05:05.083 --> 00:05:09.600 line:82%
Two, that I marry a Sardar,
and three, that my mother dies.

58
00:05:09.708 --> 00:05:12.606 line:82%
Saraswatiji, Lata, Asha and Usha

59
00:05:12.875 --> 00:05:14.708 line:82%
have served you
with their music for years.

60
00:05:14.910 --> 00:05:19.917 line:82%
But from today, Kammo,
Vimmo and I, Lajjo--

61
00:05:19.998 --> 00:05:21.194 line:82%
Hello!

62
00:05:21.245 --> 00:05:22.390 line:82%
Will serve you.

63
00:05:22.648 --> 00:05:24.313 line:82%
So without delay further

64
00:05:24.313 --> 00:05:26.917 line:82%
