had their own battle in the house.

114
00:08:08.583 --> 00:08:10.458 line:82%
It's so cold! Is the heater on?

115
00:08:10.542 --> 00:08:11.958 line:82%
You are always on, aren't you?

116
00:08:12.042 --> 00:08:13.208 line:82%
- What?
- Nothing!

117
00:08:14.167 --> 00:08:15.542 line:82%
- Will it?
- Shut up.

118
00:08:16.046 --> 00:08:18.283 line:82%
- Bet?
- Don't irritate me.

119
00:08:18.375 --> 00:08:20.000 line:82%
Chicken. It's just one dollar.

120
00:08:20.292 --> 00:08:22.833 line:82%
- What's for breakfast?
- Fruit and cereal.

121
00:08:22.917 --> 00:08:24.833 line:82%
- What?
- Cereal.

122
00:08:25.083 --> 00:08:27.167 line:82%
Has it started?
The serial, Kahani Ghar Ghar Ki?

123
00:08:27.917 --> 00:08:30.375 line:82%
Not the TV serial, the cereal we eat.

124
00:08:30.583 --> 00:08:33.333 line:82%
So what's new?
We eat that everyday.

125
00:08:33.792 --> 00:08:36.750 line:82%
Poor daughter-in-law,
she doesn't know how to make Indian food.

126
00:08:37.958 --> 00:08:39.500 line:82%
Our dear daughter-in-law, Jenny.

127
00:08:41.792 --> 00:08:44.875 line:82%
Do you know, Naina?
I saw a lovely dream last night.

128
00:08:45.417 --> 00:08:48.042 line:82%
In the dream,
I was eating hot potato flatbread,

129
00:08:49.500 --> 00:08:52.792 line:82%
with lots of white butter.
It reminded me of Chandigarh.

130
00:08:53.125 --> 00:08:57.167 line:82%
If you miss Chandigarh so much
then you must go there.

131
00:08:58.300 --> 00:09:01.833 line:82%
